[~saran] [~Yann]
There are two main type of lead (C3) shown in Minerva; c3_cod and c3_credit.

Explored the code; looked for all pieces of code that could change e-payment status of c3_cod leads. Looked at Minerva and Marol. And found that such operations could be done in Marol; all other places doesn't seem to be related to it. Especially found update_payment_status method in app/controllers/contact_api_controller line 73. Third party services can change the type of the contactc3 by sending request to that action method passing the id and status of the contactc3 in parameters. If we send "complete" status for a contactc3 there will be a check for if there are other contactc3s with the same email; course_id; in case there are then all that contactc3s will have their statuses changed to "completed" and some of them may have type equal to c3_cod. That's what i managed to find

[~azat17] Any suggested solution to prevent this; I think it is not correct to have c3_cod with complete status in our database.

[~saran] we can add a clause in that request by which not to take duplicated contactc3 which have c3_cod type . Such way i can prevent status updating of c3_cod leads in that request and further see if we get any c3_cod with complete status or not.

# Apologies if there has been confusion caused on this with my explanation. If you would rather we discuss it on Friday so we are clear; we will be happy to do so. I will try and explain more what I mean here though to give you a better idea. I have attached an example which is extremely common for address entry on a website. You can see that Postcode is asked for first; and they have the option to find address; which then normally just requires a user to enter their door number/building name. I know we don't have that functionality (as I presume it is a paid extra) and I am also aware that full postcode is our primary piece of information. However; the current format used in the design is confusing in its layout. Can we add the individual cells for each part of the address (as shown in the attachment) and make them all mandatory; keeping postcode entry first? It is clear to the User that they need to give us the full address and prevents a confusing UX (it wasn't clear to me how to write the full address into the cell in the current design)._!Sorted House - Address Example .JPG|width=402;height=389! _

AccountKit's workflow is as follow it uses emails and phone numbers where it sends codes; after which a user should enter that code and if the code is valid a user gets redirected back to their page where special callback handlers handle the data with user's token. The reason i reopened the ticket is to review one issue related to _*Terms and Condition acceptance*_. When asset_type field's value is other than 'Video' then the .lecture-preview element remain without href element and replacing function is executed on the href attribute which's null.

Found in laravel docs. Starting with MySQL 5.7; {{0000-00-00 00:00:00}} is no longer considered a valid date. As documented at the [+Laravel 5.2 upgrade guide+|https://laravel.com/docs/5.2/upgrade#upgrade-5.2.0]; all timestamp columns should receive a valid default value when you insert records into your database. You may use the {{useCurrent()}} column modifier (from Laravel 5.1.25 and above) in your migrations to default the timestamp columns to the current timestamps; or you may make the timestamps {{nullable()}} to allow null values.
[http://mysqlserverteam.com/mysql-8-0-when-to-use-utf8mb3-over-utf8mb4/|http://mysqlserverteam.com/mysql-8-0-when-to-use-utf8mb3- over-utf8mb4/]

Authorization through Google cannot be done simply through allauth. The user will have to redirect to apihi and the api will have to record the session. You should not do this; because in this case; for some users we will have authorization by tokens without sessions; and for others without tokens; but with sessions. You will need to dig into the doc: [https://developers.google.com/identity/protocols/OAuth2WebServer] and integrate it into our token authorization process. Unfortunately there is no obvious documentation in the rest-auth doc

Then I searched / studied different packages for authorization by social networks. networks; trying to apply a solution that authorized only by tokens; avoiding sessions. I even started to implement an authorization service that absolutely does not save state and does not use sessions; having previously tried to find similar solutions on the Internet - I did not find it. As a result; I quit this case; because I came to the conclusion that the solution is absolutely pointless and I did not find a similar solution in Google for this very reason.

s3 restricts access to buckets by special keys. By generating a signed url; we officially give permission to the recipient of the url to use the image for a period specified by us; i.e. Signed urls CORS is unlikely to limit.
I read a little: the dock above contained recommendations for the design of an application that works with s3. There was nothing in the documentation about structuring buckets.

The most optimal scenario would be: generating a pre-signed url on the server and returning them to the client; so that the client requests resources (photos) in s3 directly - it will remove the load from the server and without an intermediary in the face of the server; loading resources (images) from clients should be faster .
